{{citation needed|October 23 (Lunisolar)}}

{{Lunisolar October}} 
'''October 23''' is the 23rd day of month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|10月 (旧暦)|lt=October (Kannazuki)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|1=Kannazuki}}  the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜}}  day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引}} .

== Events ==
* {{ill|Kengan (Han)|ja|建安}} 5th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}}  {{ill|200|ja|200}}  {{ill|November 17|ja|11月17日}} ） – During the Han, when Prince Shangchen’s rebellion occurred, the capital battle at Guandu took place as {{ill|Yuan Shao|ja|袁紹}}  faced a night attack by {{ill|Cao Cao|ja|曹操}} .
* {{ill|Kōji (Japan)|ja|Kōji}} 1st year（{{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}}  {{ill|1555|ja|1555}}  {{ill|November 7|ja|11月7日}} ） – The era name was changed from {{ill|Tenbun|ja|天文 (元号)|lt=Tenbun|lt_ja=天文}}  to {{ill|Kōji|ja|Kōji}} .
* {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era}} 5th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}}  {{ill|1577|ja|1577}}  {{ill|December 2|ja|12月2日}} ） – {{ill|Oda Nobunaga|ja|織田信長}}  ordered {{ill|Hachiyoshi Hideyoshi|ja|羽柴秀吉|lt=Hideyoshi}}  to launch an expedition against China.
* {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永}} 6th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}}  {{ill|1629|ja|1629}}  {{ill|December 7|ja|12月7日}} ） – The Edo Shogunate banned female kabuki, female dance, and female jōruri for disrupting public order.
* {{ill|Kanbun|ja|寛文}} 9th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}}  {{ill|1669|ja|1669}}  {{ill|November 16|ja|11月16日}} ） – An Ainu chieftain, {{ill|Shakusha In|ja|シャクシャイン}} , was murdered during peace talks at Matsumae Taihira’s encampment.
* {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era}} 1st year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}}  {{ill|1868|ja|1868}}  {{ill|December 8|ja|12月8日}} ） – The Meiji government’s general affairs were reorganized: for instance, {{Enomoto Takeaki}}  and others occupied the Goryōkaku in Hakodate.

== Births ==
