'''October 23''' is the 23rd day of month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|10月 (旧暦)|lt=October (Kannazuki)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|1=Kannazuki|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/October (Lunisolar)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kannazuki|qq=}}  the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}}  day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomobiki|qq=}} .

== Events ==
* {{ill|Kengan (Han)|ja|建安|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kengan (Han)|qq=}} 5th year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]]  [[:en:200 (number)|200]]  [[:en:November 17|November 17]] ） – During the Han, when Prince Shangchen’s rebellion occurred, the capital battle at Guandu took place as [[:en:Yuan Shao|Yuan Shao]]  faced a night attack by [[:en:Cao Cao|Cao Cao]] .
* {{ill|Kōji (Japan)|1=Kōji (Muromachi period)|2=ja|3=弘治 (日本)|lt=Kōji|4=ru|5=Кодзи (Муромати)|ja|Kōji|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōji (Japan)|1=Kōji (Muromachi period)|2=ja|3=弘治 (日本)|lt=Kōji|4=ru|5=Кодзи (Муромати)|qq=}} 1st year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]]  {{ill|1555|ja|1555|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1555|qq=}}  [[:en:November 7|November 7]] ） – The era name was changed from [[:en:Tenbun|Tenbun]]  to {{ill|Kōji|ja|Kōji|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōji|qq=}} .
* [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 5th year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]]  {{ill|1577|ja|1577|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1577|qq=}}  [[:en:December 2|December 2]] ） – [[:en:Oda Nobunaga|Oda Nobunaga]]  ordered {{ill|Hachiyoshi Hideyoshi|ja|羽柴秀吉|lt=Hideyoshi|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiyoshi Hideyoshi|qq=}}  to launch an expedition against China.
* [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] 6th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]]  {{ill|1629|ja|1629|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1629|qq=}}  [[:en:December 7|December 7]] ） – The Edo Shogunate banned female kabuki, female dance, and female jōruri for disrupting public order.
* [[:en:Kanbun (era)|Kanbun]] 9th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]]  {{ill|1669|ja|1669|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1669|qq=}}  [[:en:November 16|November 16]] ） – An Ainu chieftain, {{ill|Shakusha In|ja|シャクシャイン|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shakusha In|qq=}} , was murdered during peace talks at Matsumae Taihira’s encampment.
* [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 1st year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]]  {{ill|1868|ja|1868|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1868|qq=}}  [[:en:December 8|December 8]] ） – The Meiji government’s general affairs were reorganized: for instance, {{Enomoto Takeaki|qq=}}  and others occupied the Goryōkaku in Hakodate.

